Doesn’t have to be native or anything, a mobile web client ala Nitter would be preferable if anything.

stories.text: Other than donating funds or providing remote employment, how can the tech community at large help help here? We have a lot of compute power at our fingertips, and more importantly, knowledge that surely can be utilised to assist both Ukrainians and Russians who oppose the insanity or are in the dark as to what goes on?
stories.title: Ask HN: How can the tech community help during this crisis?

stories.text: I get this question all the time for interviews, and I never have a good answer. In fact, it's possible if you do have a good answer for this question, it's because you're doing something wrong. But what do other people have?
